<div id="so_formfield_dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_" class="field fld_description fld-ro">

            <div class="label" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__field-label">
	<label for="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_">Synopsis</label><span class="req-indicator"></span>:
      </div>
            
      	 	<div class="widget" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__widget">
			<div class="notice_desc_dates">
				<span class="added">Added: <input type="hidden" name="dnf_class_values[procurement_notice][description][0][added_on]" value="2014-02-13 09:39:01">Feb 13, 2014 9:39 am</span>
					</div>
		BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF WORK: Contractor shall provide all tools, equipment, materials, labor, supervision, personnel and shall do all things necessary that will result in the connection of a water line to a new 12" water main to be installed by Indiana American Water along Howe Road into Indiana Dunes National Lakeshore and provide municipal water and fire suppression to the Good Fellow Camp.<br /><br />
ESTIMATED RANGE: In accordance with FAR Subpart 36.204, the magnitude of this requirement is estimated between $25,000 and $100,000.<br /><br />
LOCATION: Indiana Dunes National Lakeshore, 1100 N. Mineral Springs Road Porter, IN 46304.<br /><br />
The anticipated issuance date of the RFP is on or about February 28, 2014 (subject to change). The Period of Performance for this contract is thirty (30) calendar days. Be advised that this requirement may be delayed, cancelled, or revised at any time during process based on decisions related to Department of the Interior (DOI) and National Park Service (NPS) changes.<br /><br />
The RFP will be posted and available for download without charge at FedConnect (https://www.fedconnect.net) on or about February 28, 2014.<br /><br />
This is a TOTALSMALL BUSINESS SET-ASIDE under NAICS: 237110, the Small Business Size Standard for this NAICS is $33.5M.<br /><br />
THERE IS NO CHARGE FOR SOLICITATION DOCUMENTS<br /><br />
GENERAL INFORMATION:<br /><br />
THE FOLLOWING REGISTRATIONS SHALL BE COMPLETED BEFORE TIME OF AWARD. Offerors who are not registered are STRONGLY ENCOURAGED to apply for registration immediately upon receipt of this solicitation.<br /><br />
DUN AND BRADSTREET NUMBER (DUNs): To be considered for award, contractors must obtain a Dun and Bradstreet Number (DUNs). Contractors may obtain this number at 1(866)705-5711.<br /><br />
SYSTEM FOR AWARD MANAGEMENT (SAM): Federal Acquisition Regulations require that federal contractors register in the System for Award Management (SAM) database at https://www.sam.gov and enter all mandatory information into the system. Award cannot be made until the contractor has registered. Bidders are encouraged to ensure that they are registered in SAM prior to submitting their proposal.<br /><br />
THESE REGISTRATIONS WILL BE COMPLETED BEFORE TIME OF AWARD.<br /><br />
NO HARD COPY DOCUMENTS WILL BE ISSUED. Point of Contact is the Contract Specialist, Robert Sirn, Phone 330-468-2500 X309, FAX 330-468-2507, e-mail: robert_sirn@nps.gov.


